data.survey.strategy: Looking for the clues that matched across all the detectives
I first tried to get all the clues together and sort them so I had all the information available from all sources.  Then I grouped similar clues together to try to make sense of the mystery.
get all the clues in promised leads so my teammates have as much information as possible and then try to piece together what was important from there
I tried to match clues across my teammates.  Once I was fairly confident about the suspect I looked at those clues more closely
I compared three different possible scenarios in my head and I choose the one that had the most concrete sounding leads. Thus, I felt it was a partially bald Wagner who did it with a pipe cutter.
look at corroborating evidence and see what made the most sense
cross out whatever didnt seem to fit
Based it on already provided evidence
I was following the other leads.
Read everything and consider what is most likely and what would be a helpful clue I could investigate further.

Try to rule out things but that was harder than i thought since multiple things seems to fit together. Towards the end i kind of just had to pick between wagner and collins and i leans towards wagner but then still had some clues that didn't fit so i left them in since i wasn't 100% sure
I tried to go based on facts
I just went with my gut and chose what felt right
I tried to connect the clues with what seemed to be the most appropriate evidence, e.g. evidence was shown that a serrated knife was used so I worked around the serrated knife first.

I just guessed and grouped things
